						</td>\r\n									<td style=\"width:127px;\">\r\n										<p>\r\n											21:30</p>\r\n									</td>\r\n								</tr>\r\n							</tbody>\r\n						</table>\r\n						<h3>\r\n							<strong>Prices:</strong></h3>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Prices for this trip range from &euro;134-149 adult and &euro;83-90 children roundtrip.</p>\r\n						<div align=\"center\">\r\n							<hr align=\"center\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n						</div>\r\n						<h2>\r\n							<strong>Brijuni Islands National Park</strong></h2>\r\n						<p>\r\n							The&nbsp;Brijuni&nbsp;or the&nbsp;Brijuni Islands&nbsp;(also known as the&nbsp;Brionian Islands;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Italian_language\" title=\"Italian language\">Italian</a>:&nbsp;<em>Brioni</em>) are a group of fourteen small&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Island\" title=\"Island\">islands</a>&nbsp;in the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Croatia\" title=\"Croatia\">Croatian</a>&nbsp;part of the northern&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adriatic_Sea\">Adriatic Sea</a>, separated from the west coast of the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Istria\" title=\"Istria\">Istrian peninsula</a>&nbsp;by the narrow&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fa%C5%BEana\">Fažana</a>&nbsp;Strait. The largest island,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Veliki_Brijun\" title=\"Veliki Brijun\">Veliki Brijun Island</a>- Brioni Grande or Veli Brijun, lies 2&nbsp;km off the coast, the others are Mali Brijun, San Marco, Gaz, Okrugljak, Supin, Supini&#269;, Galija, Grunj, Krasnica (Vanga), Madona, Vrsar, Jerolim and Kozada. Famous for their scenic beauty, the islands are a holiday resort and a&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Croatian_National_Park\" title=\"Croatian National Park\">Croatian National Park</a>.</p>\r\n						<p>\r\n							In 1945 after&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_War_II\">World War II</a>&nbsp;the Brijuni became part of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SFR_Yugoslavia\" title=\"SFR Yugoslavia\">Yugoslavia</a>&nbsp;and President Marshal&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Josip_Broz_Tito\">Josip Broz Tito</a>&nbsp;made the Brijuni Islands his personal State Summer Residence. Almost 100 foreign heads of state visited Tito on his islands, along with film stars including&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elizabeth_Taylor\">Elizabeth Taylor</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richard_Burton\">Richard Burton</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sophia_Loren\">Sophia Loren</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carlo_Ponti\">Carlo Ponti</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gina_Lollobrigida\">Gina Lollobrigida</a>.</p>\r\n						<p>\r\n							In 1991&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Croatia\">Croatia</a>&nbsp;gained independence and made the Brijuni Islands an International Conference Center. Four hotels on&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Veliki_Brijun\" title=\"Veliki Brijun\">Veliki Brijun Island</a>&nbsp;were re-opened, as well as a Safari Park, which holds animals given to Tito, such as Sony and Lanka, two Indian elephants donated by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indira_Gandhi\">Indira Gandhi</a>.</p>\r\n						<p>\r\n							On the Brijuni Islands there are several archaeological and cultural sites worth visiting. At four sites on&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Veliki_Brijun\" title=\"Veliki Brijun\">Veliki Brijun Island</a>&nbsp;over 200&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dinosaur\">dinosaur</a>&nbsp;footprints have been discovered, which can be traced to the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cretaceous_Period\" title=\"Cretaceous Period\">Cretaceous Period</a>&nbsp;from where Brijuni Cretaceous Park gets its name. There is the 13th century AD St. Mary&#39;s Church which was built by the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Knights_Templar\">Knights Templar</a>. There are also two ancient&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ancient_Rome\" title=\"Ancient Rome\">Roman</a>&nbsp;villa remains, from the 2nd Century BC and remains of a&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Byzantine\" title=\"Byzantine\">Byzantine</a>&nbsp;palace. The last remain is Hill-fort which was a&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bronze_Age\">Bronze Age</a>&nbsp;settlement on the island that dates back to the 14th century BC.</p>\r\n						<h3>\r\n							<strong>Plan Your Visit:</strong></h3>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Visit any of the local Rabac tourist agencies to book your trip to these beautiful and historic islands. Transportation is available to and from along with expert tour guides for an enhanced experience. Hotels are located on the islands for those who want to stay overnight.</p>\r\n						<h3>\r\n							<strong>Price:</strong></h3>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Prices range from &euro; 70 to 200.</p>\r\n						<div align=\"center\">\r\n							<hr align=\"center\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n						</div>\r\n						<h2>\r\n							<strong>Visit Krk Island</strong></h2>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Among the 1185 Croatian islands, only one of them is the golden one, the Insula Aurea &ndash; the island of Krk. Located in the centre of the Kvarner bay, it is considered one of the most attractive tourist destinations. Its mild Mediterranean climate, good geographical position and variety of natural and cultural beauties gave it, even in ancient times, the name &quot;Golden Island.&quot; Its cultural heritage has given it another name &ndash; the cradle of Croatian culture, whilst at the beginning of the 20th century it gained the name the &ldquo;sixth continent.&rdquo;</p>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Krk has an unusual and varied relief, climbing from the north-western part to the south-eastern part &ndash; from picturesque gentle coves and lagoons, along fertile fields and dense forests with sub-Mediterranean vegetation, to the parts of bare limestone and real mountain landscape. On the island of Krk there are three streams and two lakes.</p>\r\n						<p>\r\n							On the highest mountain top, Obzovi (570 m), visitors may forget that they are actually on an island. Here some very specific phenomena can be found &ndash; such as the flora in Krk which includes around 1400 species of land plants, which are almost half of the total in Croatia. Its unique plant the &ldquo;Barba&scaron;ova lazarkinja&rdquo; is one of the world&#39;s rarities, and it only grows in the Ba&scaron;ka lagoon.</p>\r\n						<h3>\r\n							<strong>Plan Your Visit:</strong></h3>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Visit any of the local Rabac tourist agencies to book your trip to the wonderful island of Krk. Transportation is available to and from along with expert tour guides for an enhanced experience. Hotels are located on the islands for those who want to stay overnight.</p>\r\n						<h3>\r\n							<strong>Price:</strong></h3>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Prices range from &euro; 70 to 200.</p>\r\n						<p>\r\n							&nbsp;</p>\r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n<!-- end of main -->	</div>\r\n</div>', '<div class=\"page_inside clear\">\r\n	<div class=\"subpage clear\">\r\n<!-- MAIN -->		<div class=\"clear fullwidth_pad\" id=\"main\">\r\n			<div class=\"boxes lines_x0x0x\">\r\n				<div class=\"container clear\">\r\n					<div class=\"inner\">\r\n						<div id=\"location_submenu\">\r\n							<div class=\"links\">\r\n								<ul>\r\n									<li>\r\n										<a href=\"page.php?id=40\">Restaurants</a></li>\r\n									<li>\r\n										<a href=\"page.php?id=76\">Excursions</a></li>\r\n									<li>\r\n										<a href=\"page.php?id=77\">Events</a></li>\r\n									<li>\r\n										<a href=\"page.php?id=78\">Beaches</a></li>\r\n									<li>\r\n										<a href=\"page.php?id=79\">Shopping</a></li>\r\n									<li>\r\n										<a href=\"page.php?id=80\">Nightlife</a></li>\r\n								</ul>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n						<h1>\r\n							<strong>EXCURSIONS</strong></h1>\r\n						<h2>\r\n							<strong>Fish Picnic</strong></h2>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Do you like fresh fish, delicious wine, great music, and sailing? If you answered yes, then you will love the Fish Picnic.</p>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Sail for the day on the crystal clear Adriatic Sea and discover the beauty of the Istran Coast. Relax, swim and bathe in the sun while you discover hidden coves, small picturesque towns, and new beaches with surreal beauty.</p>\r\n						<h3>\r\n							<strong>What to Expect:</strong></h3>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Sail to the second biggest island of Cres where you will have some time to explore gothic-renaissance architecture, historic towns and beautiful beaches. Expert guides are available to share the history of the island with you.</p>\r\n						<p>\r\n							While sailing on the boat enjoy glass after glass of both red and white local Croatian wine. You can also drink locally distilled Brandy and other spirits, as well as beer. The captain and his crew will also be preparing you a freshly caught seafood meal prepared in a few delicious ways. You can expect grappa, different varieties of fish, cabbage, and fresh salad.</p>\r\n						<h3>\r\n							<strong>What to Bring:</strong></h3>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Make sure you bring a bathing suit, sunscreen, towels, snacks, and water.</p>\r\n						<h3>\r\n							<strong>Price:</strong></h3>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Prices range from &euro; 25-40 per person. The boat departs from the Rabac dock every morning.</p>\r\n						<hr />\r\n						<h2>\r\n							<strong>Postojna Cave</strong></h2>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Over one million years ago the Postojna Caves were carved out by the Pivka River that runs through Slovenia. The caves are now some of the most beautiful in the world and a favorite tourist attraction for thousands of people every year.</p>\r\n						<p>\r\n							The cave was first described in the 17<sup>th</sup> century by author Johaan Weichard Valvasor and later visited by Francis I, the first Emperor of Austria. In 1819, the caves were opened to the public and have since become one of the top tourist attractions in Slovenia.</p>\r\n						<h3>\r\n							<strong>What to Bring:</strong></h3>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Do not forget your camera, comfortable walking shoes, and a bag to carry your belongings. We also recommend packing snacks and drinks for the trip.</p>\r\n						<h3>\r\n							<strong>Plan Your Visit:</strong></h3>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Visit any of the local Rabac tourist agencies to book your trip to these magical caves. Transportation is available to and from along with expert tour guides for an enhanced experience.</p>\r\n						<h3>\r\n							<strong>Price:</strong></h3>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Prices range from &euro; 60 to 100.</p>\r\n						<div align=\"center\">\r\n							<hr align=\"center\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n						</div>\r\n						<h2>\r\n							<strong>Plitvice Lakes</strong></h2>\r\n						<p>\r\n							The Plitvice Lakes is a national park in Croatia located in the mountainous region of Lika. The lakes are divided into the 12 Upper Lakes (Gornja Jezera) and the Four Lower Lakes (Donja Jezera).&nbsp;</p>\r\n						<p>\r\n							The lakes are renowned for their distinctive colors, ranging from azure to green, grey or blue. The colors change constantly depending on the quantity of minerals or organisms in the water and the angle of sunlight.</p>\r\n						<h3>\r\n							<strong>What to Expect:</strong></h3>\r\n						<p>\r\n							The Plitvice Lakes are a four hour bus ride from the center of Rabac. The bus will pick you up early in the morning and return late in the evening. The bus ride comes complete with an expert guide that will share information on towns and architecture as you pass by on your way to the lakes.</p>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Halfway through the bus ride you will stop for a quick meal and bathroom break. Once you have arrived at the lakes you will have around 3 or 4 hours to explore the area, enjoy a ferry ride, chat with fellow travelers, and take pictures. Food and drink is available at the lakes.</p>\r\n						<h3>\r\n							<strong>What to Bring:</strong></h3>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Do not forget your camera, comfortable walking shoes, and a bag to carry your belongings. We also recommend packing snacks and drinks, and maybe a good bottle of wine for the trip home.</p>\r\n						<h3>\r\n							<strong>Plan Your Visit:</strong></h3>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Visit any of the local Rabac tourist agencies to book your trip to these beautiful and unique lakes. Transportation is available to and from along with expert tour guides for an enhanced experience.</p>\r\n						<h3>\r\n							<strong>Price:</strong></h3>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Prices range from &euro; 60 to 100.</p>\r\n						<div align=\"center\">\r\n							<hr align=\"center\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n						</div>\r\n						<h2>\r\n							<strong>The Glassboat Tour</strong></h2>\r\n						<p>\r\n							Discover the underwater world of the Adriatic Sea as you sail along the Rabac coast aboard a glass bottom boat. You will get to see both big and small fish, a wealth of flora and fauna and everything else that lives in the sea.</p>\r\n						<h3>\r\n							<strong>What to Expect:</strong></h3>\r\n						<p>\r\n							You will get to see two views of Croatia, one above water and the other below. The large, modern boat will take you on a several hour ride along the coast departing from the Rabac riva. While you&rsquo;re on board you will be offered wine, spirits, and beer. Just relax, bathe in the sun, and enjoy the views you will not soon forget.</p>\r\n						<h3>\r\n							<strong>What to Bring:</strong></h3>\r\n						<p>\r\n							We recommend you bring a camera for pictures, towel to lie on, and some snacks to munch on.</p>\r\n						<div align=\"center\">\r\n							<hr align=\"center\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n						</div>\r\n						<h2>\r\n			